{"key":"processedPost-19466271","value":{"id":19466271,"first":19466130,"last":19466789,"when":1390570575,"utime":"01/24/14 03:36 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>gman7104 said:</b><br />I made a SGFC out of a tote, with holes on all 6 sides. It does not seem to be humidified by the perlite at all, my cakes dried up.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />This is a typical new grower mistake.&nbsp; Your cakes are supposed to dry out.&nbsp; If they didn't, they wouldn't fruit.<br /><br />What this tells is that you're not properly misting.&nbsp; Even at 99% humidity, your cakes will dry out without proper misting.&nbsp; Simply increase the amount of water you're spraying on the cakes.&nbsp; The overspray from this keeps the perlite wet so it never dries out.<br />RR","title":"Re: perlite not humidifying SGFC","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}